# API Documentation

## Introduction

Base URL
The base URL for our API is: http://example.com/api/v1

### Endpoints

#### Users

- GET /users
  
Description: Get a list of all users.
Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body:
json

`[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "username": "user1"
  },
  {
    "id": 2,
    "username": "user2"
  }
]`

- GET /users/:id

Description: Get details of a specific user by ID.
Status Code: 200 OK
Body:
json

`{
  "id": 1,
  "username": "user1"
}`

- POST /users

Description: Create a new user.
Body:
json

`{
  "user": {
    "username": "new_user"
  }
}`

Response:
Status Code: 201 Created
Body:
json
`{
  "id": 3,
  "username": "new_user"
}`

- DELETE /users/:id

Description: Delete a user by ID.
Status Code: 204 No Content
#### Items

- GET /items
  
Description: Get a list of all items.

- GET /items/:id

Description: Get details of a specific item by ID.
Status Code: 200 OK

- POST /items

Description: Create a new item.

Body:
json

`{
  "item": {
    "name": "New Item Name",
    "image": "https://example.com/item-image.jpg",
    "description": "Item description",
    "deposit": 100,
    "finance_fee": 10,
    "option_to_purchase_fee": 5,
    "total_amount_payable": 200,
    "duration": 12
  }
}`

- DELETE /items/:id

Description: Delete an item by ID.
Status Code: 204 No Content

#### Reservations

- GET /reservations
  
Description: Get a list of all reservations.

- GET /reservations/:id

Description: Get details of a specific reservation by ID.
Status Code: 200 OK

- GET /users/:user_id/reservations/:id

Description: Get reservations of a specific user.
Status Code: 200 OK

- POST /reservations

Description: Create a new reservations.

Body:
json

`{
  "reservation": {
    "user_id": 1, // The ID of the user making the reservation
    "item_id": 2, // The ID of the item being reserved
    "city": "New York",
  }
}`

- DELETE /reservations/:id

Description: Delete an item by ID.
Status Code: 204 No Content

Errors

In case of an error, the API will return a JSON response with an error message and an appropriate status code.

Example Error Response:

json
Copy code
{
  "error": "User not found"
}
